---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="Home Daycare Income | Childcare Business Plan"
    description="Home daycare income potential depends on your state's capacity limits, local market rates, and CACFP participation. Get personalized estimates for your situation."
>
    <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-16 px-4">
        <!-- 1. OWNERSHIP FRAMING -->
        <section class="text-center mb-16">
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                YOUR Income Potential
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                Home daycare income isn't a fixed number—it's determined by your
                state's capacity regulations, your local market's rate
                structure, and your ability to maintain full enrollment.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- 2. FACTORS THAT AFFECT OUTCOME -->
        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                What Affects Your Income
            </h2>
            <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-600">
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Your income ceiling is set by your state's capacity limits
                    for family childcare providers. Some states allow 12
                    children with an assistant, others cap you at 6 without
                    help. This single regulation can double or halve your
                    maximum revenue, regardless of market demand.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Local market rates create the other half of the equation.
                    Affluent suburbs might support premium pricing that
                    dramatically increases your per-child revenue. Rural areas
                    or lower-income communities might require competitive
                    pricing that limits what you can charge while still filling
                    spots.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Additional revenue streams matter too. CACFP reimbursement
                    for meals can add significant income for providers serving
                    eligible families. Before and after school care, drop-in
                    rates, and summer programs create opportunities beyond
                    traditional full-time enrollment. Your actual income depends
                    on how you structure your offerings and which supplementary
                    programs your market will support.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 3. WHY GENERIC ADVICE FAILS -->
        <section class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">
                Why Online Advice Often Conflicts
            </h2>
            <div class="prose prose-lg text-gray-600">
                <p class="mb-4">
                    Generic income estimates for home daycares range from barely
                    minimum wage to six-figure incomes. Both are possible, but
                    they describe completely different regulatory environments,
                    market conditions, and business models. An estimate based on
                    California capacity limits and rates means nothing if you're
                    in Vermont.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-4">
                    The median income statistics you find online blend together
                    providers at different capacity levels, in different
                    markets, with different enrollment rates. They can't tell
                    you what's possible for you specifically—only what's average
                    across thousands of providers in vastly different
                    situations.
                </p>
                <p>
                    You need to see numbers that reflect your state's capacity
                    limits, your local market rates, and realistic enrollment
                    scenarios. That's the only way to evaluate whether a home
                    daycare represents a viable income opportunity for your
                    situation.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- 4. CTA TO CALCULATOR -->
        <section class="text-center py-12 px-8 glass-panel rounded-3xl">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
                See How Much YOU Could Make in Your State
            </h2>
            <p class="text-gray-600 mb-6">
                Get your personalized income estimate based on your state's
                family daycare regulations and local market rates.
            </p>
            <a
                href="/tools/income-builder"
                class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-full bg-teal-600 hover:bg-teal-700 text-white font-medium px-8 py-4 shadow-lg transition-all"
            >
                Use the Free Calculator →
            </a>
        </section>
    </main>
</Layout>
